## Risk Scoring

OpenSecKit uses a 3-factor risk scoring system:

```
Score = Impact × Probability × Exposure
```

| Factor | Scale | Description |
|--------|-------|-------------|
| Impact | 1-5 | Business/security impact |
| Probability | 1-5 | Likelihood of occurrence |
| Exposure | 1-5 | Attack surface exposure |

| Severity | Score Range |
|----------|-------------|
| CRITIQUE | 64-125 |
| IMPORTANT | 27-63 |
| MINEUR | 1-26 |

## The 7 Principles

| # | Principle | Description |
|---|-----------|-------------|
| I | Threat Modeling | Proactive threat analysis (STRIDE) |
| II | Risk Analysis | Scoring and prioritization |
| III | Security by Design | Built-in security controls |
| IV | Security Testing | SAST/DAST/SCA automation |
| V | Secrets Management | No secrets in code |
| VI | Audit Logging | Immutable, centralized logs |
| VII | Patch Management | Strict update SLAs |

